          "email": "qian@ddn.com",
          "date": "2023-11-07 09:01:58.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-12916 osd-ldiskfs: use workqueue to write good extent",
        "message": "LU-12916 osd-ldiskfs: use workqueue to write good extent\n\nBuilding a good full extent I/O (i.e. 1MiB) in the I/O service\nthread context once detected may make the I/O service time uneven.\nThis may result int long-tail delay.\n\nTo solve this problem, we use workqueue to build a good full\nextent I/O in an extra system workqueue thread.\n\nTest-Parameters: forbuildonly\nSigned-off-by: Qian Yingjin <qian@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I96c6bc479767001e8a4bf83b97a271ed4b705e0d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
